A yellow warning for snow and ice is in place until 10am in Essex, Suffolk, East Sussex and Kent. A yellow ice warning has also been in effect since 9pm on Thursday, and will last until 10am, striking along the east coast in the north of England and along Scotland. Forecasters say Friday morning will feature cold weather between -3C and 0 until 9am across much of the UK. Where snow falls in Scotland, Sky News forecast temperatures could fall as low as -6C due to wintry showers.